<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="a" from="1" to="4" step="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="b" from="1" to="4" step="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="c" from="1" to="4" step="1"/>
  <number name="cplus">$c+0.03*$a</number>

  
<!-- <function domain="($xA-1,$xA+1)">$m1*(x-$x1)^2+$y1</function> -->
  
  <function name="f" symbolic="true">-1/3*x^3 + $a*x^2 - 2*$b*x + 2*$a + $b</function>
  <derivative name="fP" symbolic="true">$f </derivative>
  <derivative name="fPP" symbolic="true">$fP </derivative>

</setup>

<p>
      For a given differentiable function <m>f</m>, suppose we know that <m>f($c) = <math>$$f($c)</math></m> and <m>f'(x) = <math>$fP</math></m>.
    </p>
    <ol marker="a.">
      <li>
        <p>Determine a formula for <m>L(x)</m>, the tangent line approximation to <m>y = f(x)</m> at the point <m>($c, f($c))</m>.  </p>

        <p> <m>L(x) = </m><answer>
          $$f($c) + $$fP($c)*(x-$c)
        </answer> </p> 
<!-- <p>
Given that <m>f(x) = <math>$f</math></m>, it follows that <m>f'(x) = <math>$fP</math></m>.
</p>  --> 
<!--        <m>$$f($c) + $$fP($c)*(x-$c)</m> -->
      </li> 
      <li>
        <p>
          Use the tangent line approximation you found in (a) to estimate <math simplify>f($c+0.03*$a)</math>.
        </p>  
          
        <p>
          <m><math simplify>f($c+0.03*$a)</math> \approx</m> <answer>$$f($c) + $$fP($c)*(0.03*$a) </answer>
        </p>  
      </li>  

      <li>
      <p>
        The approximation generated by the tangent line is      
        <answer>
          <choiceInput name="overunder" inline>
            <choice>greater than</choice>
            <choice>less than</choice>
            <choice>equal to</choice>
          </choiceInput>            
            <award>
              <when>$overunder.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) < 0    
              </when>
            </award>  
            <award>
              <when>$overunder.selectedIndices=2 and $$fPP($c) > 0 
              </when> 
            </award>
          </answer> 
          the true value of <m>f($cplus)</m>, since <m>f''($c)</m> is 
          <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason1" inline>
              <choice>positive</choice>
              <choice>zero</choice>
              <choice>negative</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0       
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=3 and $$fPP($c) < 0 
                </when>
              </award>
          </answer>, so near <m>x = $c</m>, <m>f</m> is
          <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason2" inline>
              <choice>concave up</choice>
              <choice>linear</choice>
              <choice>concave down</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0       
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason2.selectedIndices=3 and $$fPP($c) < 0 
                </when>
              </award>
          </answer>, which makes the tangent line to <m>f</m> at the point <m>($c,f($c))</m> lie
     <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason3" inline>
              <choice>below</choice>
              <choice>above</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason3.selectedIndices=2 and $$fPP($c) < 0    
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason3.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0 
                </when> 
              </award>
      </answer>   
    the curve.
        </p>
      </li>  
    </ol>  
